latestIgtvVideos.title: My midi skirt collection ❤️
latestIgtvVideos.caption: It’s the item in my wardrobe that takes up the most space without a doubt but it’s also the item I wear the most! 😁 I purchased my first midi skirt a few years ago from @primark and haven’t looked back since! ☺️ I love how easy they are to style and how they suit any body shape! It has definitely helped me find ‘my style my as sorts. Most skirts featured are from @newlook @primark @nastygal and @tuclothing - all of which I recommend buying midi skirts from! 🎉 My favourite style/cut of a midi skirt is bias cut as I find it suits my figure the best! 👍🏼 Have you got a item of clothing in your wardrobe that love as much as me and my midi skirts? 😅

latestIgtvVideos.title: At home latte ☕️
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I’m a massive coffee drinker and lover, I can’t get enough of the stuff especially lattes, they’re my favourite! ❤️ I recently treated myself to a ‘lockdown’ proper coffee machine complete with milk frother and it’s been one of the best purchases of 2020. As I can’t go to any coffee shops for a while, I thought I’d become an ‘at home barrister’ and perfect my latte art skills (they’re nonexistent at this current moment). I thought I’d do a funny IGTV of how I make my lattes, I hope this proves entertaining more than informative if anything 😂👍🏼 Hope you enjoy this as it was fun to film and edit 📸
My coffee machine is; https://www.argos.co.uk/product/8477958
Milk jug; @sainsburyshome https://www.sainsburys.co.uk/gol-ui/product/sainsburys-home-drury-lane-milk-jug-134435430-p

latestIgtvVideos.title: Come flatlay and edit with me... 📸
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Something a little different from me today but I wanted to show you how I typically do a flatlay and then edit my photos! I don’t know if it’ll be of any use to anyone but it was different to film and edit. I’m a massive lover of flatlays and think they’re such a personal thing to create so how I do them is what works for me! 👍🏼
I was using my @olympus_pengeneration E-PL8 camera to shoot with and imported my photos to my phone via the Olympus OI.Share app. I then edited my photo via @googlesnapseed 📸
Any other questions, please don’t hesitate to comment or message me 🖤

latestIgtvVideos.title: There’s nothing holdin’ me back... 💃🏻
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Not going to lie, I’ve been feeling pretty shit the past few days. For the first time in 6 months + I had to admit I felt depressed again which isn’t an easy thing to say. My mind has been in a complete scramble not being able to make sense of any of my thoughts. I’m trying to take every day as it comes and be positive wherever I can. With so much uncertainty at the moment, I want to at least have something good in every day so I decided to dance away to my favourite @shawnmendes song and not hold anything back. Gosh it fells good and I hope it brings a bit of happiness or joy to your day too! ❤️ Please feel free to laugh at my dance moves which clearly shouldn’t be thrown by a 24 year old 😅
Stay strong, healthy and safe everyone. We’ve got this, even if it does mean dancing ourselves silly 😜

latestIgtvVideos.title: Everyday Make-up Routine 💄
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I don’t claim to be any form of a make-up artist or know much about make-up in fact but I have my own way to do my make-up everyday so I thought I’d show you! 💄 
I love make-up (I probably own too much of it to be honest) and enjoy using it but by no means rely on it in order to feel good about myself and I’m comfortable enough to to go out bare faced more days than with make-up which is a massive thing for me 😊🎉 It was really fun to film this and who knows if it does well then there might be more beauty videos in the future...
All products used are listed below (my links aren’t working but will hopefully add them in ASAP) - 👍🏼
